## vercel.json Structure

```json
{
  "version": 2,
  "build": {
    "env": {
      "NODE_VERSION": "20",
      "CI": "false",              // prevents CRA from treating warnings as errors
      "GENERATE_SOURCEMAP": "false"
    }
  },
  "installCommand": "npm install --prefix banking_api_server && npm install --prefix banking_api_ui",
  "buildCommand": "cd banking_api_ui && npm run build",
  "outputDirectory": "banking_api_ui/build",
  "rewrites": [
    { "source": "/api/:path*", "destination": "/api/handler" },
    { "source": "/((?!api/).*)", "destination": "/index.html" }
  ]
}
```

**Rules:**
- The rewrite order matters — `/api/:path*` must come before the SPA catch-all.
- Do NOT add route patterns for individual API routes — all go to `/api/handler`.
- Adding a new route in Express = just add `app.use('/api/new-route', ...)` in `server.js`. No `vercel.json` change needed.

